<b>Structured_text</b> may be composed of other instances of <b>Structured_text</b> or 
<express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Text_representation_item"/> as content, in a tree structure.  
A <b>Structured_text</b> shall be acyclic.  The <b>Structured_text</b> should at least provide content at the lowest level of 
the structure. 
</p><note>
This part of ISO 10303 is exchanging the content of a document, not its presentation format.
</note>

<example number="1">
An example of <b>Structured_text</b> is an extract from an  
<express_ref linkend="Document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/> in SGML, in which each portion of the  
<express_ref linkend="Document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/> has a known structure.
</example>
<example number="2">
<p>
<b>Structured_text</b> objects can be chapters, titles, paragraphs, sentences or structured markup.
</p>
</example>

</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text.content_markup">
specifies a role of the 
<express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_source_identification"/> 
for the <b>Structured_text</b>. 
The <b>content_markup</b> identifies the computer interpretable element type of the content.  Plain text shall be a string encoded 
according to clause 7.3.3 of ISO 10303-21.  Plain text shall be identified by the following contents of the 
<express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_source_identification"/> 
referenced by <b>content_markup</b>: 
<express_ref linkend="External_item_identification_assignment:arm:External_item_identification_assignment_arm.External_source_identification.source_type"/> is "text markup tag", code_value is "plain text", <express_ref linkend="Analytical_model:arm:Analytical_model_arm.Analytical_model_definition.reference_document"/> is "ISO 10303-210".
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text.structured_text_content"><p>
specifies a role of the <b>Structured_text</b> for the <b>Structured_text</b>. 
There may be one or more entries in the <b>structured_text_content</b> for a particular <b>Structured_text</b>.  The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</p><note>
<p>
<b>structured_text_content</b> would only not be provided if there was no need to specify lower level markup within the current 
markup or if <b>plain_text_content</b> were provided.
</p>
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text.precedent_structured_text"><p>
specifies a role of the <b>Structured_text</b> for the <b>Structured_text</b>.  
This role is appropriate when both <b>Structured_text</b> are helping to compose a higher level <b>Structured_text</b> 
or are referenced by an <express_ref linkend="Document_definition:arm:Document_definition_arm.Document_definition"/>.  
The value of this attribute need not be specified. 
</p><note>
<p>
<b>precedent_structured_text</b> is provided to ensure the correct sequencing of text contents.
</p>
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Structured_text.plain_text_content"><p>
specifies a role of the <express_ref linkend="Characteristic:arm:Characteristic_arm.Text_representation_item"/> for the <b>Structured_text</b>. The <b>plain_text_content</b> need not be provided for the <b>Structured_text</b>. The value of this attribute need not be specified. 
</p><note>
<p>
<b>plain_text_content</b> would only not be provided if there was a need to specify lower level markup within the current markup.
</p>
</note>
</ext_description>
-->
<!-- +++++++++++ Surface_finish_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Surface_finish_specification">
A <b>Surface_finish_specification</b> is a type of 
<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Material_specification"/> that is a collection of the 
properties applicable to surface textures or 
coatings either for a product in-process or a completed product.
</ext_description>

<!-- +++++++++++ Test_specification +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Test_specification">
	A <b>Test_specification</b> is a type of 
	<express_ref linkend="Specification_document:arm:Specification_document_arm.Specification_definition"/> that 
	provides information about the physical or functional testing of an 
	<express_ref linkend="Product_identification:arm:Product_identification_arm.Product"/>.
</ext_description>

<!-- WR1 -->
<ext_description linkend="Specification_document_arm.Test_specification.wr:WR1">
	The
	<express_ref linkend="Product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition.additional_characterization"/>
	shall not be populated.
</ext_description>

